The paper discusses a consensus protocol for electronic payment systems, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with security and fault tolerance, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The protocol is designed to achieve high throughput and scalability, which relates to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to building consensus protocols, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
